race.comment: MISS HIMALAYA (8) tried hard at Wodonga last start when up on speed, boxing on for third. She's got versatility and can look to be positive again from the low gate which will suit. This looks a nice race for her. JINGU EXPRESS (12) was a bit flat as favourite last time but had been good fresh and can improve third up with a bit of early luck from the gate. WARLIST (10) finished midfield when resuming from a spell last start over 1200m at Wodonga. Steps up in distance today and can contest on an each-way basis. TIMBOLTON (11) is battling away and wasn't beaten far last time out. He should be thereabouts.
